      "message": "My original code predates the published M3K Linux port. These names are just holdovers from my early work; I\u0027m fine with changing them.\n\nThere\u0027s a minor issue: scrolling per se currently isn\u0027t implemented, the button code just treats pressing on the upper/lower areas of the scrollbar as BUTTON_UP/BUTTON_DOWN. I intend to fix this later, but it\u0027s not a priority for me right now.\n\nIt would be possible to implement scrolling AND keep this behaviour, which would give this port more usable buttons than the Linux port. But I\u0027m not sure this is a good idea myself. It might be useful mainly for the games.",
      "parentUuid": "0fff7c83_f7bb5307",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 24,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 35,
        "endChar": 34
