      "writtenOn": "2021-03-03T21:32:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If I\u0027m doing my math correctly, a 64-bit OST will take 24,372 years to wrap, even running at 24MHz.  So we probably don\u0027t need to worry about wrapping.\n\nAlso, it\u0027s best to add +1 to us to guarantee that we will always delay at least as long as the requested time.  (otherwise we could under-delay by a fraction of a us..  on the other hand, you\u0027re using 64-bit math, which probably makes up the difference and then some..)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 137,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 139,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "1b9555859e46be85f1625e0c82f2bc6e6d71875f",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
